<!-- Facts Start -->
<div class="container-xxl py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 wow fadeIn" data-wow-delay="0.1s">
                <div class="h-100 bg-dark p-4 p-xl-5">
                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between mb-4">
                        <div class="btn-square rounded-circle" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; background: #000000;">
                            <img class="img-fluid" src="~/img/icon/placeholder.png" alt="Icon">
                        </div>
                        <h1 class="display-1 mb-0" style="color: #000000;">01</h1>
                    </div>
                    <h5 class="text-white">Location</h5>
                    <hr class="w-25">
                    <span>The Fag el-Gamous cemetery is a massive 125-hectare Graeco-Roman necropolis located on the eastern edge of the Fayoum Depression, containing over a thousand documented burials exhumed over twenty-five years of excavations.</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 wow fadeIn" data-wow-delay="0.3s">
                <div class="h-100 bg-dark p-4 p-xl-5">
                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between mb-4">
                        <div class="btn-square rounded-circle" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; background: #000000;">
                            <img class="img-fluid" src="~/img/icon/zeroa.png" alt="Icon">
                        </div>
                        <h1 class="display-1 mb-0" style="color: #000000;">02</h1>
                    </div>
                    <h5 class="text-white">Density</h5>
                    <hr class="w-25">
                    <span>Burial density at the site varies between 1.3 and 3.0 burials per square meter, with the majority of the burials found in rectangular shafts at depths of 0.3–3.0 m, oriented on an east–west axis.</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 wow fadeIn" data-wow-delay="0.5s">
                <div class="h-100 bg-dark p-4 p-xl-5">
                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between mb-4">
                        <div class="btn-square rounded-circle" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; background: #000000;">
                            <img class="img-fluid" src="~/img/icon/rex2.0.png" alt="Icon">
                        </div>
                        <h1 class="display-1 mb-0" style="color: #000000;">03</h1>
                    </div>
                    <h5 class="text-white">Carbon Dating</h5>
                    <hr class="w-25">
                    <span>AMS radiocarbon dating of available samples shows that the oldest head-east burial dates to AD 79-230, and the oldest head-west burial dates to AD 128-284, with the head-east and head-west burial practices coexisting for at least 200 years.</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<!-- Facts Start -->
<!-- About Start -->
